      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(install): verify node binary after auto-install and suppress ioctl errors",
        "body": "## Problem\n\nThe Node.js auto-installer reports \"Node.js v22 installed\" without verifying the binary is actually available on PATH. On WSL2 Ubuntu 24.04, the NodeSource setup script produces ioctl errors (interactive terminal prompts in a non-interactive context), apt may fail silently, but the installer prints a success message and then immediately crashes with \"Node.js v22+ is required.\"\n\nTwo root causes:\n1. The NodeSource setup script (`bash \"$tmp\"`) runs without `DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive`, so it attempts interactive terminal operations that produce ioctl errors on WSL2\n2. The installer prints `ui_success \"Node.js v24 installed\"` unconditionally after the apt call, without verifying `node` is on PATH\n\n## Fix\n\n1. Pass `DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive` to the NodeSource setup script execution (both root and sudo paths)\n2. Run `activate_supported_node_on_path` and verify the active node meets the minimum version requirement (`node_is_at_least_required`) before printing the success message. If node is missing or too old, report the actual failure and exit instead of falsely reporting success.\n\nFixes #73837\n\n## Real behavior proof\nBehavior addressed: the Node.js auto-installer now verifies the node binary is actually on PATH and meets the minimum version after package installation before reporting success, and passes DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive to the NodeSource setup script to suppress ioctl errors on WSL2.\nReal environment tested: local source checkout of openclaw/openclaw at commit aaadf721e3 (current upstream/main) on Linux x86_64, Node v26.0.0, bash 5.2.37.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: extracted the `node_is_at_least_required`, `parse_node_version_components`, and `parse_node_version_components_for_binary` functions from the patched `scripts/install.sh` and exercised the post-install verification logic under three conditions: (1) node present and meets minimum, (2) node binary missing (empty PATH), (3) post-install guard sequence from `install_node()`.\nEvidence after fix: terminal output copied below.\n\n```console\n$ node -v\nv26.0.0\n\n$ bash -c '\nNODE_MIN_MAJOR=22; NODE_MIN_MINOR=14; NODE_MIN_VERSION=\"${NODE_MIN_MAJOR}.${NODE_MIN_MINOR}\"; NODE_DEFAULT_MAJOR=24\nparse_node_version_components_for_binary() {\n    local node_bin=\"${1:-node}\"\n    if ! command -v \"$node_bin\" &> /dev/null && [[ ! -x \"$node_bin\" ]]; then return 1; fi\n    local version major minor\n    version=\"$(\"$node_bin\" -v 2>/dev/null || true)\"\n    major=\"${version#v}\"; major=\"${major%%.*}\"\n    minor=\"${version#v}\"; minor=\"${minor#*.}\"; minor=\"${minor%%.*}\"\n    if [[ ! \"$major\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]]; then return 1; fi\n    echo \"$major $minor\"\n}\nparse_node_version_components() {\n    if ! command -v node &> /dev/null; then return 1; fi\n    parse_node_version_components_for_binary node\n}\nnode_is_at_least_required() {\n    local version_components major minor\n    version_components=\"$(parse_node_version_components || true)\"\n    read -r major minor <<< \"$version_components\"\n    if [[ ! \"$major\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ || ! \"$minor\" =~ ^[0-9]+$ ]]; then return 1; fi\n    if [[ \"$major\" -gt \"$NODE_MIN_MAJOR\" ]]; then return 0; fi\n    if [[ \"$major\" -eq \"$NODE_MIN_MAJOR\" && \"$minor\" -ge \"$NODE_MIN_MINOR\" ]]; then return 0; fi\n    return 1\n}\necho \"=== Test 1: Current node meets requirement ===\"\necho \"Node version: $(node -v)\"\necho \"Min required: v${NODE_MIN_VERSION}\"\nif node_is_at_least_required; then\n    echo \"PASS: node_is_at_least_required returned 0 (success)\"\nelse\n    echo \"FAIL: node_is_at_least_required returned 1\"\nfi\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Test 2: Simulate missing node binary (empty PATH) ===\"\nOLD_PATH=\"$PATH\"; PATH=\"/nonexistent\"\nif node_is_at_least_required; then\n    echo \"FAIL: should have returned 1 for missing node\"\nelse\n    active_version=\"$(node -v 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\")\"\n    echo \"PASS: node_is_at_least_required returned 1 (node binary: ${active_version})\"\n    echo \"Would print: Node.js v${NODE_MIN_VERSION}+ required but found ${active_version} after install\"\nfi\nPATH=\"$OLD_PATH\"\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Test 3: Post-install guard logic (patched version) ===\"\necho \"Simulating install_node() post-install sequence...\"\nif node_is_at_least_required; then\n    echo \"Post-install check passed - would print: Node.js v${NODE_DEFAULT_MAJOR} installed\"\nelse\n    echo \"Post-install check FAILED - would exit 1 with error\"\nfi\n'\n=== Test 1: Current node meets requirement ===\nNode version: v26.0.0\nMin required: v22.14\nPASS: node_is_at_least_required returned 0 (success)\n\n=== Test 2: Simulate missing node binary (empty PATH) ===\nPASS: node_is_at_least_required returned 1 (node binary: not found)\nWould print: Node.js v22.14+ required but found not found after install\n\n=== Test 3: Post-install guard logic (patched version) ===\nSimulating install_node() post-install sequence...\nPost-install check passed - would print: Node.js v24 installed\n```\n\nDEBIAN_FRONTEND is now set in both NodeSource setup paths:\n```console\n$ grep -n \"DEBIAN_FRONTEND\" scripts/install.sh\n594:        env DEBIAN_FRONTEND=\"${DEBIAN_FRONTEND:-noninteractive}\" NEEDRESTART_MODE=\"${NEEDRESTART_MODE:-a}\" apt-get \"$@\"\n596:        sudo env DEBIAN_FRONTEND=\"${DEBIAN_FRONTEND:-noninteractive}\" NEEDRESTART_MODE=\"${NEEDRESTART_MODE:-a}\" apt-get \"$@\"\n1633:                run_quiet_step \"Configuring NodeSource repository\" env DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive bash \"$tmp\"\n1636:                run_quiet_step \"Configuring NodeSource repository\" sudo DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive bash \"$tmp\"\n2774:        export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=\"${DEBIAN_FRONTEND:-noninteractive}\"\n```\n\nLines 1633 and 1636 are the new additions. Lines 594 and 596 show the existing pattern in `apt_get()` that this fix follows.\n\nObserved result after fix: the post-install guard correctly detects a valid node (Test 1: v26.0.0 >= v22.14, returns 0), correctly catches a missing node binary (Test 2: PATH emptied, returns 1 with \"not found\"), and the install_node() guard sequence works end-to-end (Test 3: passes with current node). The success message is now gated behind `node_is_at_least_required`, and DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive is passed to the NodeSource setup script on both root and sudo paths.\nWhat was not tested: actual WSL2 Ubuntu 24.04 reproduction of the ioctl error (Node.js is already installed on this machine). Could not test a real failed install scenario where apt succeeds but the binary is not on PATH. The fix uses the same `node_is_at_least_required` helper and `DEBIAN_FRONTEND` pattern already used elsewhere in the script.\n",
